data.name: CutoutInfoLabel.Text
data.value: This option will draw a dim rectangle around the rasterbation graphic of each page. The border will make it considerably easier to cut away the empty margins. If you plan not to cut out the margins, you should uncheck this.

data.name: PrintInfoLabel.Text
data.value: When printing the image in Adobe Reader, choose Page scaling: Fit to paper at the options window that comes up. If you chose horizontal paper alignment, also make sure Auto-Rotate and Center is selected. Most printers cannot print to the margins of the paper - these settings ensure that all the images will be completely printed.
